I came to the following problem. I have a set of documents, that have a &quot;token&quot; key, which values are specific scopes:

    &quot;token&quot; : &quot;foo&quot;
    &quot;token&quot; : &quot;foo.bar&quot;
    &quot;token&quot; : &quot;foo.bar.joe&quot;
    &quot;token&quot; : &quot;foo.baz&quot;
    &quot;token&quot; : &quot;foo.baz.qux&quot;
    &quot;token&quot; : &quot;foo.joe.rex&quot;

And so on. What I want to achieve is to be able to get all the documents, that are contained into a given token. In other words, querying with &quot;foo.bar.joe&quot;, has to give me back &quot;foo.bar.joe&quot;, &quot;foo.bar&quot; and &quot;foo&quot; only.

With MySQL this is relatively straightforward:

    SELECT * 
    FROM table 
    WHERE (LOCATE(CONCAT(token, &#39;.&#39;), &#39;foo.bar.joe.&#39;) = 1);

But I can&#39;t get to an easy solution for elasticsearch.

Thanks in advance.

I&#39;m trying to use JAVA to write some queries with elastic search but I&#39;m having trouble even with the most simple of queries.

Here&#39;s what I&#39;ve right now:

    public class App {
        TransportClient client;
    
        public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
            App app = new App();
    
            app.startUp();
            app.deleteIndex();
            app.insercionesIniciales();
            app.selectByUser(&quot;kimchy&quot;);
    
            app.close();
        }
    
        private void deleteIndex() {
            DeleteIndexResponse deleteResponse = client.admin().indices().delete(new DeleteIndexRequest(&quot;twitter&quot;)).actionGet();
        }
    
        public void startUp() throws UnknownHostException {
            client = new PreBuiltTransportClient(Settings.EMPTY)
                    .addTransportAddress(new TransportAddress(InetAddress.getByName(&quot;127.0.0.1&quot;), 9300));
        }
    
        public void insercionesIniciales() throws IOException {
            IndexResponse response = client.prepareIndex(&quot;twitter&quot;, &quot;tweet&quot;, &quot;1&quot;)
                    .setSource(jsonBuilder()
